  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Preoperative radiotherapy and pelvic surgery is recommended to many patients with rectal
      cancer. For men there are theoretical reasons to believe that the treatment may effect
      hormone levels, spermatogenesis, sexual function and wellbeing. To address these questions a
      longitudinal observational study was initiated where patients can choose to take part in one,
      two or three parts of the study. The three different parts are blood tests, questionnaires
      and semen samples.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
